,Recommended,241410,8667997,"Posted: 11 January, 2014",all,GnomeSlice,"Anyone who has ever played and enjoyed 'Age of War' should take a serious look at CastleStorm.  The basic premise is the same; you and your opponent control castles on either side of the map, and the goal is to send troops across to capture your opponent's flag. Each castle is also equipped with a ballista which can be loaded with all kinds of interesting ammunition, like javelins, stones, potions, and sheep.  The ballista can be used to kill enemy troops, or to destroy rooms in their castle (a la angry birds).There's a host of different units, ammunition, castle rooms, and magic spells to choose from, and lots of stuff to upgrade.  And if you like, you can design your own castle to fit the rooms (and by extension bonuses) that you want.It's all presented very well, with excellent graphics, great sound design, and a fantastic soundtrack from Waterflame (who incidentally created the song used in Age of War as well).  There are a lot of levels to play through, with bonus challenges to keep you coming back, and a scoring system that encourages you to find the most efficient way to complete a level.The gameplay itself is also surprisingly deep.  Building your own castle lets you choose what types of units you want to use in the upcoming battle, and you can also swap out your ballista projectiles and magical spells to find the ones that suit your needs.Definitely recommended, I've been having a lot of fun with this one."
