,Recommended,241410,8492074,"Posted: 1 January, 2014",all,Mr. Matt,"Holy crap. I expected this game to be a turd, but it's quite addictive. I just finished all of the single player content for this game (including DLCs), and it was a lot of fun. A lot of people are ragging on the story. I found it to be cute/funny. It's not serious at all and is quite ridiculous, in a good way. The style of comedy is similar to Swords & Soldiers if you've played that. In this game, you shoot hordes of enemies with a ballista, summon troops to attack the enemy castle and keep enemy troops away from your castle, all while blasting at the enemy's castle to destroy rooms which represent each combat bonus or enemy type the enemy has. Don't like their dragons? Shoot the dragon's nest off the top of the castle; problem solved! The castle-blasting is like Angry Birds, which I actually don't like, but I enjoyed the way it's done in this game. Oh, and you get money when you complete a level and can replay levels for more cash, upgrading everything from heroes you spawn and control zoomed in between the castles, the troops you spawn, your combat bonuses, etc.TL;DR Get the complete pack for this game with all its DLC whenever you see it on sale for just under seven bucks. I had a great time with it. A diamond in the rough."
