76561198004695007,Not Recommended,241410,11760972,"Posted: 17 August, 2014",all,Gray Grim,"Only buy this game when it is on sale. It is not worth $10. The $5 I bought it for is about right. This game could have been great, but instead is merely mediocre, and all because of the poor unit mechanics.The storyline is fun and engaging, but any actual control over your hero is close to imaginary.The response time to shield against attacks is laughable, you can only see 3 feet in front of you, and you give up control over your best weapon (the ballista)Ground based unit fights are done in an unusual style. each unit stops to fight only one other letting all other enemis past.For example, if you have 2 soldiers against 1 enemy one of your soldiers and theirs will engage and your second will walk right past.This might not seem like much until you get larger units with splash attacks. Trolls and the like can kill several of your units will one hit but only one of yours even gets to attack.This combat is even more poorly implemented when you add in the ballista and flying units. The ballista shots damage your own units, and it can easily become impossible to fire without hitting your own unitsThe flying combat is even more disjointed and tacked on. I have never had a single ranged ground unit take out a flyer. You have to shoot them down yourself.Coupled with said flyers ducking and bobbing randomly, as well as dealing splash damage attacks (and one hit killing most units), this is a huge oversight and in many cases ruins and otherwise fun game time.The organization of the game is foolishly repetative. In both kingdom/royal guard, and Viking/viking elites factions the units are almost interchangeable, but upgrades must be bought separately.Separate upgrades must be bought for all of the support buildings as well, even though these are exactly the same across all classes. This is true of some of the Heros/Heroins too.Too long; Didn't readThis game could have been great, but the lack of testing and poorly implemented ideas make this mediocre. Only buy when half off (it's not worth the full $10)."
