,Recommended,241410,23211357,"Posted: 25 May, 2016",all,Mr.,One question:Do you like Angry Birds?For PC?
,Not Recommended,241410,8812557,"Posted: 22 January, 2014",all,Upsilon,"Let me start by saying: I'm a total sucker for a good indie game. In my opinion, indie games are TRUE video gaming. None of this 50GB, HD, 1,000FPS, DX50, PERFECT GRAPHIX 'N SOOPUR AWSUM CINIMATICZ! The moment I saw CS for sale, I could of sworn it was a steal. I jumped into its wacky, colorful world that left my sides splitting with laughter and the time of my life in gameplay....but something went wrong about half way through; the game lost it's charm almost immediately by a few blantantly bad ideas and campaign design.Plot 10/10I love the idea of the story. 2 kingdoms in seemingly endless war were destroying one another. The goddess of the game's universe was so distrought, she cries, but - intead of tears - 2 gems were crystilized from her eyes and fell to earth. These strange metals seemed to sate the bloodlust of the 2 kings that held them and there was peace. However, someone has tampered with the gems, and war as again surfaced. Quite the creative setting, if you ask me. It has a few twists and is told well. Can't ask for much more out of a story in a simple game as this. You'll also be laughing thoughout at the zany writing and character design. It has a humor that is rarely tapped into nowadays.Graphics 10/10Just by looking at the screenshots, it's easy to tell this game is delightfully beautiful. With a wide palette of colors, Zen Studios truly made a charming world. The visuals remind me of an old Disney movie. Character models, level design, art; across the board, the visuals are at zenith.Sound 10/10The sound is up to par with the best of full budget, AAA titles. Voice cast is also well done. Most notably, the game's soundtrack is legendary! It's made by a young man that goes by the pseudonym WaterFlame89 on Youtube. Don't miss out on tracks like ""Donkey Island"", ""Title Theme"", ""Happy War"", ""Storming Castles"", or ""Long, long ago...""! Remember old songs like the Goof Troop theme? They were so catchy, uplifting, and always made you smile; even during your toughest days. WaterFlame89 has ressurected that long, lost art of music composition. I almost cry when I hear them. ;~;http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LGoYX1FMq-A&index=2&list=PL5xceeTDjuOPHBIQnD4TdpNljEggDFfsvGameplay 6/10Many will note the influences taken from Angry Birds ( or if you really want to go back, ""Crush the Castle). This is a good example of ""inspired"" not ""ripped off"". You custom build your castle, or take presets to battle, adding rooms that each buff your viability. If a certain room is destroyed, it's contribution ceases i.e. if you have a barracks room destroyed, you can't train your grunts. There is a ballista that you can control to launch a variety of projectiles either at the enemy castle, or at the enemy troops. There's also an option to train troops of your own and smash the front gate of the castle; revealing their flag, or even spawning a hero that you control temporarily. Capture the enemies flag with your troops, or annihilate the castle to win. I was completely hooked by the gameplay and it's bronze/silver/gold ranking, challenge system. With great replayability, visuals, engrossing sound track, and humorous, intriguing story, what could possibly go wrong?CS gains momentum as you fire it up and play, but somewhere near the mid point of the game, it changes which faction you play as. The first mission of this new faction was dreadful! The game starts taking a bunch of cheap shots on you. You're forced to play a hero class and kill a certain number of enemies without dying. However, the controls as a hero in the first place are utterly terrible, clunky, counter-intuitive, and worst of all, you die fairly quickly. I had to change the game to EASY just to barely squeeze my way past this debacle. Worse yet, when you reach this point of the game, it's out of new features. You've already seen all the weapons, all the new troops, and all the new rooms. The rest of the game is playing the same mission against a fairly cheap AI whose troops 100% of the time STOMP on yours, forcing you to use your ballista on enemy troops while the enemy ballista takes free shots on your castle. Another annoying thing is your heros talk EVERYTIME they attack. One girl shouts ""MAXIMUM DAMAGE"" when you use her alternate attack, then shouts ""Oh, no!"" EVERYTIME she's hit. ""MAXIMUM DAMA- OH NO! MAXIMUM DAMA- OH NO! MAXIMUM DAMA- OH NO! MAXIMUM DAMA- OH NO! MAXIMUM DAMA- OH NO! MAXIMUM DAMA- OH NO! MAXIMUM DAMA- OH NO!"" Just from that quote, you can see how hero gameplay works; it's almost unplayable entirely.The VerdictCS has a lot of incredible things going for it in terms of music, gameplay, sound, visuals, and story. The issue is that it runs out of fun before it runs out of content with bad level design and cheap AI in later missions. It was even enough to make me quit the game. I'm on the fence of whether I should recommend or not. Final score is 6/10. It's terrific!...until those few missions ruin it. Then Castle Storm becomes nothing but a slightly above-average game. It really pains me to talk about this game that way."
