,Recommended,241410,10856858,"Posted: 26 June, 2014",all,outrider42,"This game is basically a tower defense version of Angry Birds. This game can be surprisingly addictive and it can be challenging at times if you don't level up the right things before battle. You can plan out your entire castle, and how you build it can be very important. Do you build redundant rooms in case they destroy one? Where is the best place for your most prized rooms? Because if you lose certain room, you lose the benefit of their use, and unlike Command and Conquer style games, there is no way to rebuild any part of your castle during the battle. This changes how you strategize for battle, and puts a great importance on protecting the castle while attacking. And the combination of attacking with units and your own catapult weapon is pretty intriguing. There is a pretty good balance between these, you really cannot neglect your units or catapult weapons too much.If I do have a complaint, it is that the game likes giving you a lot of levels that restrict you to just one task, like levels where you cannot use any soldiers, or ""hero"" levels that restrict you to just controlling your hero. The hero levels can be very hard later on if you fail to level that particular hero, it makes a huge difference. But while these hero levels can be a change of pace, the game is still at its best when the levels feature castle vs castle play.The game is colorful, but still a bit gory if you are thinking about getting it for kids. The story is a total after thought, you are not playing this for any story. Even so, it can be mildly entertaining at times and is full of juvenile humor. The music is pretty good.Overall it is a pretty solid game."
