76561198006758332,Recommended,241410,11942099,"Posted: 31 August, 2014",all,gudbrandur,"A nice game that will bring you several hours worth of strategic/gunnery fun.What you have here is a game that is a mix of a few elements.A 2d strategy game where you build units that then run automatically towards the enemy to do some killing and looting.A physics shooter (Like Angry birds).A base builder.And a mini platformer.You win by destroying the enemy base with your ballista or invading it with your units to capture his flag.How does all this work? Pretty inituitively actually.Just hold down the left mouse button to fire a stream of javelins from your ballista, whilst you click the other mouse buttons and the number buttons to perform your other duties. You can headshot Barbarians, build knights and cast spells all at the same time!But that does sound like a heavy brain toll, aiming can be intense alone, but making troops? Triggering special attacks? Alternating ammo types? With all this variety comes an interesting amount of customisability.When you build your castle, you need to set up protection for the building components that influence your gameplay, theres troop structures that enable your units, upgrade structures that strengthen your defenses and units, and then jusr raw materials that you place to protect those important elements.Exactly which parts you pick will heavily influence your game, if you dont like to maintain troops then you can forego them nearly completely (the campaign does require you to have a little of everything), and spend all of your resources on upgrading your ballista. If youre not too sharp on constant ballista vigil and would rather lead and command an army, you can upgrade the troops and even your own ""hero"" unit, which you can summon to the field to fight on the frontline. Thse elements then click together interestingly, a ballista focused player can develop a few key units to protect his front gate that then when the gate is clear shoot the enemy caste in tandem with your ballista bolts. Alternatively you can go for the other victory option that is ""capture the flag"", where you build frontline units to storm the enemy caste, and then cover them with hero summoning and ballista attacks. Another strategy is to focus on the special munitions available to ballistas, these munitions often have poor rate of fire, but you can make up for that by going into hero mode between cooldowns.Included is a mildly entertaining campaign with a variety of missions that challenge you to use the different elements of the game in concert or seperately. It wont win any prizes for originality story wise but what did you expect from a game with so many unique gameplay mechanics?In other words, this rather simple looking game has a deceptive amount of depth to it, allowing the player to develop his own brand of strategy.If youre a fan of strategic games, and want to play something completely different from the norm for a while, this is a game you will enjoy.Gameplay: 5/5.Surprisingly deep strategy and a large pool of options to pick from. Several interesting mechanics.Art: 4/5.For an underdog company, the game is exceptional. The sprites are easy to read and iconic, there is a lot of animations and a fair amount of agreeable classissism in the designs. its got nothing on the industry titans of videogaming, but for an indie game it is well above the minimal acceptable threshhold.Story 3/5.Average. Lighthearted comedy mixed with a standardised plot of ""Bad things happen, hero saves day, goes on journey to find source of bad things, hero saves the day again."" The plot was just charming enough to get an average score for being ""Classic"".Sound 3/5.The background music is nearly entirely ""light action-symphonies"". The music is constant but not distracting. The very basic soundract and the simple voice-acting was enough to set the mood and setting, mission accomplished.Accessibility 2/5.A found that this problem deserves a notice here. I found myself clicking a lot of unnessesary buttons, especially in menu's and the castle builder. There is no auto save for the castle builder that I know-off.Total score: 68.Pick it up, play it and enjoy it for the mechanics and the strategy. I can even reccomend the DLC's for some extra challenges and charming character interactions, its worth a few days of fun for sure."
,Recommended,241410,9627397,"Posted: 25 March, 2014",all,ZenosyX,"This is a great casual game which is satisfying to kill time with. Slightly addictive, if you're the slightest competative and want to beat everything with a perfect score.The gameplay itself is very simple, sadly I must admit it just feels like an upgrade to ""Castle Defender"" (the old flash game) since the core of the game have the same setup. But the humor and goofy graphics still make it into a more proper and nice game. if you're unsure if it's your type of game just go try ""Castle Defender"", which feels a bit like an alpha to this game... but I recommend it nonetheless. I really enjoyed the casual strategical thinking of it with the silly humor always close. This is as said a few times now, like a massive upgrade from that addictive olf flash game.The soundtrack of it is also a big bonus; relaxing, goofy and cheerful. Perfect elements for a casual game.Price: Personally I'd say they ask for a bit too much, especially since there's a ""free alpha"" in flash online... but if you get a discount for it then I'd say it could be fun to try at least."
