,Recommended,241410,8675715,"Posted: 12 January, 2014",all,Dycerius,"This game is pretty easy to learn but interesting to master. It follows the tower defense mechanics where you have a castle that needs to be protected. You are able to spawn units to attack the opponents flag, which is near their castle. You have a ballista that you use to shoot out different projectiles according to your level and current progress. There are heroes you can spawn for 10+ seconds to alter the battlefield a long with spells to control, aid or destroy your opponent.The core gameplay is a mixture of sending troops to the middle of the battlefield, using spells and heroes to control the flow and using your ballista to shoot out rocks or eagles or whatever, to destroy the opponents castle.Extra feature is the ability to upgrade your abilities, units, spells and heroes. You can build and design your own castle and put the rooms you need according to your strategy. If you loose a room in the battle you also loose its ability/feature while your in the match. So if you loose the archer room, you can't spawn archer anymore. So a very strategic aspect right there.In multiplayer you can unlock and play the other factions which opens up new heroes, units and method of play."
