,Recommended,241410,1023767,"Posted: 29 September, 2013",all,Jorkfriend,"Quite a nice little game, I got it on sale for like 5 bucks and it was definitely worth the asking price. Basically there's one of two factions, Kingdom and Norse, each have their own campaign which will take you at least 8 hours if you ignore all the side missions. Obviously each side has their own attacks, minions, spells, etc.The goal changes from level to level but most of the time it's you vs. your enemy, with the victory conditions typically being to either destroy your enemies castle (which is well done I might add) or capture their flag by breaking down their gate and sending a ground troop to snag it. There's a good variety in minions, attacks, and spells so you'll definitely be experimenting with your loadout to see what you like best. You get gold throughout the game and you spend that on upgrades for whatever you want.There's also 3 other gamemodes aside from campaign, Survival, Skirmish, and Hero Survival. Survival is a lot of fun but if you do TOO well it starts to get boring and you'll want to lose on purpose, but that's not exclusive to this game. Skirmish is more like a regular match where you can customize your experience a little bit. Hero Survival sucks dino dong because the ""take control of hero"" combat is incredibly basic.You can also customize your own castles which is pretty cool, although it's clear it was put in as an afterthought at the last minute. Still, it works and the game is better for it to be in the very basic state that it's in rather than not at all. There's two dlcs available for this game, haven't gotten them yet so I can't comment on how good or bad those are.Final, sad fun fact: This game plays more like a worms game than all the ♥♥♥♥♥♥ modern worms game Team17 ♥♥♥♥♥ out nowadays."
