76561197971291045,Recommended,241410,28717943,"Posted: 27 December, 2016",all,Thrill,"What a whole lot of fun this game is! It reminds me of the modernization of that ancient Flash game where you defend your castle from stick figures by tossing them into the sky, Defend Your Castle. (Which I guess was a precursor to the Clicker genre, though that particular comparison does not hold with this game.) I'm sure others have pointed to more recent antecedents.The video pretty much gives you everything you need to go on. Stuff if running toward your castle, and you need to keep your ballista firing at the enemy while you send wave after wave of your own troops and occasionally enter the fray with your own hero. There are basic RPGesque improvements to be made, troops and spells and projectiles to be unlocked, that sort of thing. You can also modify your castle to maximize bonuses and structural integrity, but that seemed a little clunky. There isn't really deep strategy at work here--it's much more about tempo management and, of course, your aim.The campaigns are very good, with three or four very different mission types interspersed at good intervals. Boss battles are interesting and require different tactics and so forth. I blew through the main ones in one sitting (~7 hours) on Normal difficulty (thanks, staycation!) and may go back and try them at higher levels. I just picked up two more campaigns as DLC, which I'm looking forward to.All of the bells and whistles are there--cutscenes look good, models look good, jaunty music sounds good. It's a very polished, straightforward kind of game!"
