,Recommended,241410,29236043,Posted: 13 January,all,Ezah,"CastleStorm is a solid little game that is a derivative of Castle Crush -- that is, the game that Angry Birds' formula is based off of. Gameplay consists of 2 different castles pitted against each other, with an arsenal of projectiles, soldiers, and spells ready to crush the opponent's castle. It's more of a real time version; instead of trying to destroy everything in 1-2 shots, you continuously wear down the castle walls to eventually destroy rooms while also juggling funneling an army at their gates to steal their flag and shooting down enemy projectiles and soldiers to keep them from doing the same.For $4, I didn't expect much, but the gameplay is solid when playing against the AI, and the story can be humorous, although the missions jump all over the place. If you're looking for something akin to the flash game Castle Crush (or Angry Birds), I recommend giving this a go. It's not quite the same, but will definitely scratch that itch and is worth checking out on sale. I give it a 6.5/10."
