,Recommended,241410,33882749,Posted: 29 July,all,NathanPandaGuy,"If you are looking to but the Complete Edition then DONT. You can get the exact same stuff for 2p cheaper if you buy the game and the DLC seperately.Other than that it is a great game, i originally bought this game back on my Xbox 360 and from what I can remember it was a blast playing with friends. You need to defend your castle and destroy the opponent's castle using troops (which can include large trolls and bird things), projectiles and yourself. The projectiles vary from regular arrows to rocks that split into more rocks to exploding apples. If you get bored you can create your own castle with different rooms.The campaign is really good, and can help you get better at the game. It will really help you if you try to do all of the bonus missions as they help you remember to get those headshots that one-hit-kill most low level enemies and get you extra coins. The coins can be used to upgrade your troops, projectiles and other things. However, these upgrades will not be in effect whilst in multiplayer."
